inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS_max_results
inputs.info: Maximum number of entries returned on one result page. The page size can never be larger than 250 entries.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS_min_access_role
inputs.info: The minimum access role for the user in the returned entries. Accepted values are 'owner' & 'reader'

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS_page_token
inputs.info: Token specifying which result page to return.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS_show_deleted
inputs.info: Whether to include deleted calendar list entries in the result.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS_show_hidden
inputs.info: Whether to show hidden entries.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS_sync_token
inputs.info: Token obtained from the nextSyncToken field returned on the last page of results from the previous list request.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_calendar_id
inputs.info: Identifier of the Google Calendar. Use 'primary' for the currently logged in user's primary calendar.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_query
inputs.info: Search term to find events that match these terms in the event's summary, description, location, attendee's displayName, attendee's email, organizer's displayName, organizer's email, etc if needed.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_max_results
inputs.info: Maximum number of events returned on one result page. The page size can never be larger than 2500 events. The default value is 10.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_order_by
inputs.info: The order of the events returned in the result. Acceptable values are 'startTime' and 'updated'.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_show_deleted
inputs.info: Whether to include deleted events (with status equals 'cancelled') in the result.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_single_events
inputs.info: Whether to expand recurring events into instances and only return single one-off events and instances of recurring events, but not the underlying recurring events themselves.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_timeMax
inputs.info: Upper bound (exclusive) for an event's start time to filter by. Accepts multiple formats:, 1. ISO format with timezone (e.g., 2024-12-06T13:00:00Z), 2. Comma-separated format (e.g., 2024,12,06,13,00,00), 3. Simple datetime format (e.g., 2024-12-06 13:00:00)

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_timeMin
inputs.info: Lower bound (exclusive) for an event's end time to filter by. Accepts multiple formats:, 1. ISO format with timezone (e.g., 2024-12-06T13:00:00Z), 2. Comma-separated format (e.g., 2024,12,06,13,00,00), 3. Simple datetime format (e.g., 2024-12-06 13:00:00)

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_updated_min
inputs.info: Lower bound for an event's last modification time to filter by. Accepts multiple formats:, 1. ISO format with timezone (e.g., 2024-12-06T13:00:00Z), 2. Comma-separated format (e.g., 2024,12,06,13,00,00), 3. Simple datetime format (e.g., 2024-12-06 13:00:00)

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_event_types
inputs.info: List of event types to return. Possible values are: default, outOfOffice, focusTime, workingLocation.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_EVENT_page_token
inputs.info: Token specifying which result page to return. Optional.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_DUPLICATE_CALENDAR_summary
inputs.info: Title of the calendar to be duplicated.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_REMOVE_ATTENDEE_calendar_id
inputs.info: ID of the Google Calendar

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_REMOVE_ATTENDEE_event_id
inputs.info: ID of the event

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_REMOVE_ATTENDEE_attendee_email
inputs.info: Email address of the attendee to be removed

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_GET_CALENDAR_calendar_id
inputs.info: The ID of the Google Calendar that needs to be fetched. Default is 'primary'.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_description
inputs.info: Description of the event. Can contain HTML. Optional.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_eventType
inputs.info: Type of the event, immutable post-creation. Currently, only 'default'

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_create_meeting_room
inputs.info: If true, a Google Meet link is created and added to the event.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_guestsCanSeeOtherGuests
inputs.info: Whether attendees other than the organizer can see who the event's attendees are.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_guestsCanInviteOthers
inputs.info: Whether attendees other than the organizer can invite others to the event.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_location
inputs.info: Geographic location of the event as free-form text.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_summary
inputs.info: Summary (title) of the event.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_transparency
inputs.info: 'opaque' (busy) or 'transparent' (available).

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_visibility
inputs.info: Event visibility: 'default', 'public', 'private', or 'confidential'.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_timezone
inputs.info: IANA timezone name (e.g., 'America/New_York'). Required if datetime is naive. If datetime includes timezone info (Z or offset), this field is optional and defaults to UTC.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_recurrence
inputs.info: List of RRULE, EXRULE, RDATE, EXDATE lines for recurring events.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_guests_can_modify
inputs.info: If True, guests can modify the event.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_attendees
inputs.info: List of attendee emails (strings).

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_send_updates
inputs.info: Defaults to True. Whether to send updates to the attendees.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_start_datetime
inputs.info: Naive date/time (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS) with NO offsets or Z. e.g. '2025-01-16T13:00:00'

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_event_duration_hour
inputs.info: Number of hours (0-24).

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_event_duration_minutes
inputs.info: Number of minutes (0-59).

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_calendar_id
inputs.info: The ID of the Google Calendar. `primary` for interacting with the primary calendar.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_DELETE_EVENT_calendar_id
inputs.info: ID of the Google Calendar

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_DELETE_EVENT_event_id
inputs.info: ID of the event to be deleted

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_FREE_SLOTS_time_min
inputs.info: The start datetime of the interval for the query. Supports multiple formats:, 1. ISO format with timezone (e.g., 2024-12-06T13:00:00Z), 2. Comma-separated format (e.g., 2024,12,06,13,00,00), 3. Simple datetime format (e.g., 2024-12-06 13:00:00)

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_FREE_SLOTS_time_max
inputs.info: The end datetime of the interval for the query. Supports multiple formats:, 1. ISO format with timezone (e.g., 2024-12-06T13:00:00Z), 2. Comma-separated format (e.g., 2024,12,06,13,00,00), 3. Simple datetime format (e.g., 2024-12-06 13:00:00)

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_FREE_SLOTS_timezone
inputs.info: Time zone used in the response. Optional. The default is UTC.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_FREE_SLOTS_group_expansion_max
inputs.info: Maximal number of calendar identifiers to be provided for a single group. Optional. An error is returned for a group with more members than this value. Maximum value is 100.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_FREE_SLOTS_calendar_expansion_max
inputs.info: Maximal number of calendars for which FreeBusy information is to be provided. Optional. Maximum value is 50.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_FIND_FREE_SLOTS_items
inputs.info: List of calendars ids for which to fetch

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_QUICK_ADD_calendar_id
inputs.info: Calendar identifier. To list calendars to retrieve calendar IDs use relevant tools. To access the primary calendar of the currently logged in user, use the 'primary' keyword.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_QUICK_ADD_text
inputs.info: The text describing the event to be created.

inputs.name: GOOGLECALENDAR_QUICK_ADD_send_updates
